---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const title = "About ZeroUpload — The Converter That Never Uploads";
const description =
  "ZeroUpload is a file converter that runs 100% in your browser. Learn who we are, why we built a privacy-first converter, and how it works.";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 pt-16 pb-20">
    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">About ZeroUpload</h1>

    <div class="article-body mt-8 space-y-4 text-stone leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        <strong>ZeroUpload converts your files without ever uploading them.</strong>
      </p>
      <p>
        Most "free online converters" quietly send your private files — photos,
        scans, contracts, voice memos — to a company's servers to do the work. We
        thought that was backwards. Your files are nobody's business but yours.
      </p>
      <p>
        So we built ZeroUpload on a single, uncompromising rule:
        <strong>your files never leave your device.</strong>
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-ink">
        How that's possible: edge computing in your browser
      </h2>
      <p>
        Modern browsers are powerful computers. Using technologies like the
        Canvas API and WebAssembly (WASM) — the same engines that power
        professional desktop software — ZeroUpload performs every conversion
        locally, inside your own browser, on your own processor and memory.
      </p>
      <p>
        Your file is read from your device, transformed in memory, and handed
        straight back to you as a download. It is never transmitted across the
        internet. There is no upload step, no server queue, and nothing for us to
        store, see, or leak.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-ink">What this means for you</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc space-y-1 pl-5">
        <li><strong>100% private.</strong> We can't read your files because we never receive them.</li>
        <li><strong>Works offline.</strong> Load a page, disconnect your internet, and it still converts — the ultimate proof that nothing is being uploaded.</li>
        <li><strong>Free and unlimited.</strong> Because the work runs on your device, there are no server costs — so there are no paywalls, no "2 free conversions" walls, and no sign-ups.</li>
        <li><strong>Fast.</strong> No upload/download round trip. Conversion is instant.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-ink">Our promise</h2>
      <p>
        ZeroUpload will never add a feature that uploads your files. The name is
        the promise. If you ever want to verify our claims, open your browser's
        Network tab while converting — you'll see zero upload requests — or read
        our source code.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-ink">Get in touch</h2>
      <p>
        Questions or ideas? Reach us at <strong>support@zeroupload.app</strong>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .article-body :global(a) {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
  .article-body :global(strong) {
    color: var(--color-ink);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
</style>
